obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47540)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47540&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Special Protection Group`
  line `Act, 1988.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st August, 1988, vide notification No. S.O. 735(E), dated 1st August, 1988, See Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47541)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1991, s. 3, for "his immediate family" (w.e.f. 25-9-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47541&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "active duty" in relation to a member of the Group means any duty as such member during the`
  line `period when he is posted to physically protect the Prime Minister of India and the members of ^1`
  line [his
  line `immediate family or a former Prime Minister and the members of his immediate family], wherever he`
  line `or they may be;`
  line
  line `(b) "Director" means the Director of the Group appointed under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "Group" means the Special Protection Group constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) "member of the Group" means a person who has been appointed to the Group by the`
  line `prescribed authority whether before or after the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "members of immediate family" means wife, husband, children and parents;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "proximate security" means protection provided from close quarters, during journey by road,`
  line `rail, aircraft, watercraft or on foot or any other means of transport and shall include the places of`
  line `functions, engagements, residence or halt and shall comprise ring round teams, isolation cordons, the`
  line `sterile zone around, and the rostrum and access control to the person or members of his immediate`
  line family;
  line
  line `(h) all words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47542)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Members subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47542&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Group shall be subject to this Act, wherever`
  line `he may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47543)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Group.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47543&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) There shall be an armed force of the Union called the Special`
  line `Protection Group for providing proximate security to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister and members of his immediate family residing with him at his official`
  line `residence; and`
  line
  line `(b) any former Prime Minister and such members of his immediate family as are residing with`
  line `him at the residence allotted to him, for a period of five years from the date he ceases to hold the`
  line `office of Prime Minister.]`
  line
  line `(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) any former Prime Minister or any member of the immediate family of the Prime Minister or`
  line `of a former Prime Minister may decline proximate security;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) where the proximate security is withdrawn from a former Prime Minister, such proximate`
  line `security shall also stand withdrawn from members of immediate family of such former Prime`
  line `Minister:]`
  line
  line `Provided that where the level of threat faced by any member of the immediate family of a former`
  line `Prime Minister warrants proximate security or any other security, such security shall be provided to that`
  line member.]
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Group shall be constituted in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and the terms and conditions of service of the members of the Group shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any person or any member of any other armed`
  line `force of the Union may be appointed to the Group by the Central Government by a general or special`
  line `order and for such period as may be specified in such order, and the person so appointed shall, during the`
  line `period of his appointment, be deemed to be a member of the Group, and the provisions of this Act shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply to such person or member.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2019, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-12-2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, for clause (b), ibid (w.e.f. 10-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47544)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Control, direction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2003, s. 3, for "Deputy Directors, Assistant Directors, Joint Assistant Directors" (w.e.f. 13-3-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47544&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and control of the Group shall`
  line `vest in, and be exercised by, the Central Government and subject thereto and to the provisions of this Act`
  line `and the rules, the command and supervision of the Group shall vest in an officer to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government as the Director of the Group.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall, in the discharge of his duties under this Act, be assisted by such number of`
  line `^1[Inspectors General, Deputy Inspectors General, Assistant Inspectors General] and other officers as may`
  line `be appointed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47545)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liability for service in and outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47545&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Group shall be liable to serve`
  line `in any part of India as well as outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47546)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Members of the Group always on active duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47546&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Group, not on leave or`
  line `under suspension, shall, for all purposes of this Act, be always on active duty and may at any time be`
  line `employed or deployed in any manner which is consistent with the duties and responsibilities of the Group`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47547)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Resignation and withdrawal from the post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47547&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No member of the Group shall be at liberty—`
  line
  line `(a) to resign his appointment during the terms of his engagement; or`
  line
  line `(b) to withdraw himself from all or any of the duties of his appointment,`
  line
  line `except with the previous permission in writing of the prescribed authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47548)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Tenure of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47548&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Group shall hold office during the pleasure of the`
  line President.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47549)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Restrictions respecting right to from associations, freedom of speech, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47549&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of`
  line `the Group shall, without the previous sanction in writing of the Central Government or of the prescribed`
  line authority,—
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not of a purely social, recreational or religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or organisation`
  line `is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) or whether any book, letter or`
  line `document is a communication or publication in the bona fide discharge of his duties or is a purely literary,`
  line `artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature under clause (c), the decision of the Central`
  line `Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Group shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by any body of persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (47550)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Termination of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47550&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The prescribed authority may, by order in writing, terminate the`
  line `appointment of any member of the Group in the public interest and such termination shall be deemed to`
  line `be discharged simpliciter and shall not amount to dismissal or removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (47551)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47551&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the Group aggrieved by an order under section 11 may, within`
  line `thirty days from the date of such order, prefer an appeal to a Board to be constituted by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of such persons as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Board shall be final and shall not be called in question in any court or tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (47552)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Powers and duties conferable on members of the Group.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47552&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct that, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations as may be specified in that order, any member of the Group may exercise or discharge such`
  line `powers or duties as may be specified in the said order for giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (47553)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Assistance to Group.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47553&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every Ministry and Department of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or the Union territory Administration, every Indian Mission, every`
  line `local or other authority or every civil or military authority to act in aid of the Director or any member of`
  line `the Group whenever called upon to do so in furtherance of the duties and responsibilities assigned to such`
  line `Director or member.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (47554)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47554&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Group or any member thereof on whom powers have been conferred or duties have been`
  line `imposed under this Act, or any order issued or any rule made thereunder for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or purported to be done or omitted to be done in pursuance of this Act or any order issued or`
  line `any rule made thereunder or any order issued under any such rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (47555)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47555&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the Group shall be constituted and the terms and conditions of service of`
  line `its members under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the authorities to be prescribed under section 8, sub-section (1) of section 10 and section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature of the communication or publication under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the purposes, other than political purposes, for which a person subject to this Act shall not`
  line `participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any demonstration under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the persons who shall be members of the Board under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (47556)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Laying of orders and rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47556&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every order issued under section 13 and every rule made under`
  line `section 16 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or made, before each House of Parliament`
  line `while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the order or the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the order or rule should not be made, the order or rule shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order or`
  line rule.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (47557)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Provision as to existing Special Protection Group.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970&sectionId=47557&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_79_00001_198834_1517807325970
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Special Protection Group in`
  line `existence at the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be the Group constituted under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The members of the Special Protection Group in existence at the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to have been appointed as such under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Anything done or any action taken before the commencement of this Act in relation to the`
  line `constitution of the Special Protection Group referred to in sub-section (1) and in relation to any person`
  line `appointed, shall be as valid and as effective in law as if such thing or action was done or taken under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
